%N A108770 Numbers k such that k^2 + (k+1)^2 is a brilliant number.
%C A108770 Consecutive terms are (254,255) (4099,4100) (11159,11160) (25094,25095) (31754,31755) (40189,40190) ... Conjecture: There are infinitely many consecutive values.
%H A108770 Harvey P. Dale, <a href="/A108770/b108770.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%e A108770 92 is a term because 92^2 + 93^2 = 17113 = 109*157 and both of its
%e A108770 factors have three digits.
%t A108770 Select[Range[1600],With[{f=Flatten[Table[#[[1]],#[[2]]]&/@FactorInteger[#^2+(#+1)^2]]},Length[f]==2&&IntegerLength[f[[1]]]==IntegerLength[f[[2]]]]&] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, May 17 2026 *)
